# The entire point of DH is to turn an insecure channel into a secure channel without actually exchanging the shared
# single key. It takes advantage of the discrete logarithm problem(DLP) to establish a shared secret among two parties.
# You communicate g, p, A, B over the insecure channel, where A = g^a mod p, B = g^b mod p, a and b are the secret 
# values known to themselves. The shared secret S = (g^a)^b mod p. A can calculate it by B^a mod p and B can have it 
# by A^b mod p. Voila!
# DLP ensures that even if an attacker intercepts g, p, A, B it will be very hard for him to iterate over all the powers
# of g to get to the secret because the number of values to iterate increases exponentially with n (number of bits in p).
# 2^n possibilities. If p is 2048 bits long the search space is 2^2048 an incredibly large number.

